
• The purpose of your program
1) multithreaded version of MapReduce to solve the "word count statistics" using consumer and producer threads
2) with flag option, print out log info into the file "log.txt"
3) output result to result.txt

• How to compile the program
1）run terminal
2）change to current directory
3）run the command "make"
The makefile will automatically generate a executable wcs

• Any assumptions outside this document
None


• What exactly your program does
phase1: create producer & consumer threads and shared queue
phase2: producer read input and put it into the shared queue
        consumer catch info from the queue and get the word count
phase3: main thread output the result to a final file

